com.ebay.lightning.core.beans

Class LightningResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ebay.lightning.core.beans.LightningResponse
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class LightningResponse
extends Object
implements Serializable
    The LightningResponse class defines the interface for the task agreed by the client and core. The class also contains LightningResponse.SuccessResponse to define a successful task, which is identified by a HTTP response code of '200' and LightningResponse.FailedResponse to define a failed task.
    Author:
    shashukla
    See Also:
    LightningRequest, LightningResponse.SuccessResponse, LightningResponse.FailedResponse, BatchReport, Serialized Form
